
  <sn><md>### Pedogenesis

- The pedogenic processes are extremely `complex`, as well as `dynamic`, involving many `physical, chemical and biological reactions`. 
- The pedogenic process vary from one place to other depending on various ++external and internal factors++ like `temperature, wind, humidity, capillary movement of water, microbial decomposition and the nature of bed rock`. 
- The collective `interaction` of various soil forming `factors` under various `environmental conditions` represent ++certain recognised soil forming processes++.
</md></sn>
